The Zimbabwe captain holds the catch, and an 83 run partnership is broken

commentary: Nyumbu to O'Brien, OUT Waller holds a catch! He would have been under some pressure as this ball rocketed towards him. Kevin O'Brien had jumped down the crease at Nyumbu, who came round the wicket, but the bat turned in his hands as he aimed down the ground. He still got a decent enough connection, but not enough to get the ball past Waller, who set himself under the chance at long off and managed to hold on. That'll be a relief for him.

commentary: Masakadza to Mooney, OUT a maiden international wicket for Wellington Masakadza! And it took a good catch out in the deep to complete it. Mooney bent low down and then aimed a slog sweep at the Tobacco Stand on the Western side of the ground, but got rather more height than distance. Jongwe was the fielder out there, and he initially ran in before backpedalling a couple of steps and setting himself for the catch. He held on cleanly, and Wellington bent down on one knee midpitch in celebration

commentary: Murtagh to Sikandar Raza, 2 runs, OUT drama! Is there another twist in this tale? Raza lofted a length delivery out to deep cover, where it fell safely. Joyce's throw from the deep went to Porterfield at cover, who relayed it to the keeper, catching the batsman well short.
